The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Sept. 28 (PTI): Bombay High Court today termed a police investigation into a Solapur robbery as casual and referred the case to the state home secretary for action.           
	The court said an officer not below the rank of sub-divisional police officer should carry out further investigations. The case, in which a chargesheet has been filed, pertains to a robbery in the house of an elderly couple in Solapur district on July 15 last year.                   
	 Banaskantha (PTI): A Pakistani teenager, who crossed the Indo-Pak border to meet his relatives in Gujarat, was detained by the Border Security Force at a village in Patan, Gujarat, on Saturday.                   
	 Madurai (PTI): A vigilance inspector has been arrested in Madurai for allegedly taking Rs 1.20 lakh as bribe from a civil assistant surgeon to drop a corruption case. Perumal Pandi had asked the doctor, Ashok Kumar, to pay him Rs 12 lakh but settled for Rs 5 lakh, police said.                  
	 Coimbatore (PTI): Twelve Nigerians, staying in Tirupur even after the expiry of their visas, have been arrested. The arrests were made on a complaint lodged by a resident of Kannagi Nagar after an argument with one of them.
                                                                                                                                              
